The government of Kenya has added one mission, that of eradicating female genital mutilation by 2030. As the world marked the international day against FGM, Kenya held its national conference in Narok, which is one of the most affected counties. Similar forums were held in other counties including Samburu and Garissa where the prevalence of the practice remains a concern. Here now are some of the voices of ant?ti FGM crusaders.